  "doc_id": "44972",
  "text": "Hesperidin is a flavanonol that structurally lacks the C(2)-C(3) double bond in the C-ring. This compound only slightly affects vascular relaxation. Planar flavonoid structures are believed to express potent vasorelaxation effects [CITATION_1] . The relationship between the structure and activity of flavonoids and their aglycones have been previously reported in antioxidant research [CITATION_2] ; however, their activities in coronary arteries have not been elucidated. In this study, we discovered that the aglycones of PF flavonoids may be involved in effecting relaxation in the porcine coronary artery.",
